BY CLICKING "I AGREE", OR BY TAKING ANY STEP TO ACCESS OR IN ANY WAY USE THE CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES VRISK PLATFORM OR TO ACCESS, DOWNLOAD, INSTALL, COPY OR IN ANY WAY USE THE VRISK™ SOFTWARE, YOU, AS THE END USER: (1) REPRESENT THAT YOU ARE OF THE LEGAL AGE OF MAJORITY IN YOUR JURISDICTION; (2) AGREE TO BE BOUND BY THE TERMS OF THIS AGREEMENT; AND (3) IF APPLICABLE, AGREE THAT YOU ARE AUTHORIZED TO ACCEPT THE TERMS AND CONDITIONS OF THIS AGREEMENT ON BEHALF OF SOME OTHER PERSON OR LEGAL ENTITY, AND WARRANT THAT YOU HAVE FULL AUTHORITY TO BIND SUCH PERSON OR LEGAL ENTITY TO THE TERMS AND CONDITIONS SET FORTH HEREIN.


DEFINITIONS

Software
For purposes of this Agreement, “Software” is defined as any software program which is used by a device which directs the processor of such device to perform specified actions or operations, including any and all Updates, Upgrades and similar activities.

End User
For purposes of this Agreement, “End User” is the person who actually accesses or in any way uses the CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES VRISK platform or who accesses, downloads, installs, copies or in any way uses the VRISK Software either on their own behalf or who legally accesses or in any way uses the CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES VRISK platform or who accesses, downloads, installs, copies or in any way uses the VRISK Software on behalf of some other person or organization of any kind, including but not limited to, an employer, without regard to the nature or legal or organizational form of such person or organization. “End User” further includes any such other person or organization of any kind, including but not limited to, an employer, without regard to the nature or legal or organizational form of such person or organization, for whom the CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES VRISK platform or VRISK Software is accessed, downloaded, installed, copied or in any way used, and any such access, download, install, copy or use in any way of the CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES VRISK website or VRISK Software in such manner operates as acceptance of the terms and conditions of this Agreement by such other person or organization of any kind, on whose behalf the CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES VRISK website or VRISK Software was accessed, downloaded, installed, copied or in any way used, and it is further represented by such other person or organization that the person who accessed, downloaded, installed, copied or in any way used the CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES VRISK website or VRISK Software on behalf of the person or organization was authorized to do so on behalf of the other person or organization.

Student
For purposes of this Agreement, "Student" includes, but is not limited to, any person who is enrolled in the Pace University Enterprise Cybersecurity course.

Organization
For purposes of this Agreement, "Organization" includes, but is not limited to, business and governmental entities of any kind, such as a sole proprietorship, partnership, limited liability company, corporation, association, joint stock company, trust, joint venture, labor organization, unincorporated organization or governmental authority.

Device
For purposes of this Agreement, a “Device” is any type of equipment capable of processing data, for which the VRISK Software was designed or may be used, and where the VRISK Software will be installed and/or used, such equipment including, but not being limited to: any equipment which uses software, such as computers of any kind (whether referred to as personal computers, desktops, laptops or in any other manner), workstations, personal digital assistants, smartphones, cell phones, handheld devices, toasters, printers, televisions or any other electronic equipment of any kind which is capable of using the VRISK Software.


I. GRANT OF LICENSE

A. The CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES VRISK platform and the VRISK Software shall be referred to collectively as the “VRISK Software” hereinafter in this Agreement, except in such instances where it is necessary to distinguish between the platform and the software.

B. Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, and except as otherwise provided in this Agreement, CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES hereby grants to End User a non-exclusive, non-transferable right to use the VRISK Software solely for Educational purposes with the Pace University Enterprise Cybersecurity program. End User acknowledges that the VRISK Software and all related information is and shall at all times remain proprietary to CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES. End User is hereby granted rights to Updates and Upgrades only as specified in this Agreement or any related attachment hereto, and for such time and under such terms and conditions as specified herein.

C. The information provided on the CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES VRISK platform, along with the use thereof, is intended for educational and training purposes only. Further, the content in and use of the VRISK Software is intended for educational and training purposes only.


II. RESTRICTIONS ON USE

