D. End User agrees to not remove any copyright, patent or trademark notices on or associated with the VRISK Software nor to remove any proprietary restrictions from the VRISK Software.


V.  COLLECTION OF DATA AND INFORMATION; VALIDATION OF USE AND SYSTEMS

A. End User is hereby notified that the VRISK Software will collect certain information about users (including user generated: usernames, passwords, and email addresses), log connection metadata (including but not limited to IP addresses and browser information), and data relating to each user’s performance on VRISK challenges, for the purposes of: improving the VRISK Software and/or other software and products; engaging in or providing other services which may or may not be associated with the VRISK Software; adapting the VRISK Software to user preferences; and to discover and prevent unlicensed and/or illegal use of the VRISK Software.

B. End User agrees that CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES may use any and all files, code, memory or software or information collected only in the manner described herein, and only for the purposes stated herein.

C. CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES and the VRISK Software, in conjunction with the service provided pursuant to the terms of this Agreement, will collect End User’s IP address in order to allow monitoring of licenses as well as to perform checks and detect possible incidents related to the VRISK Software and its use. End User hereby acknowledges and authorizes the processing of the IP addresses by CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES in relation to the use of the VRISK Software.

D. End User agrees, for purposes of contracting and using the VRISK Software, that End User will provide certain personal data to CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES. Thus, End User is hereby informed of and consents to the processing of End User’s personal data as set forth herein. Any such personal data obtained by CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES will be safeguarded and handled by CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES pursuant to applicable legislation and CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES’s privacy policy.

E. End User hereby acknowledges, agrees to and authorizes CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES to collect and use statistics on End Users use of the VRISK Software, as well as technical information End User provides in relation to the use of the VRISK Software. CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES agrees not to use this information in any manner which will personally identify End User, except as otherwise provided, required or authorized pursuant to the terms of this Agreement.


VI. MODIFICATIONS TO PRODUCTS AND SERVICES; UPDATES

A. End User acknowledges and agrees that during the contracted period, CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES may change or modify the VRISK Software or services offered in connection therewith, in the sole and complete discretion of CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES. End User further agrees to accept any and all changes without making any demand for compensation of any kind. CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES reserves the right to notify End User, in CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES’s sole and complete discretion, of any such changes. End User further acknowledges and agrees that CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES may provide updates, changes or the like to the VRISK Software.

B. End User, upon agreeing to and accepting the terms and conditions set forth in this Agreement, further agrees to and accepts all modifications to the service and the VRISK Software authorized pursuant to the terms of this Agreement.


VII. AUDIT OF END USER

CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES reserves the right, in its sole and complete discretion, at any time and at its own expense, to conduct an audit regarding End User’s compliance with the terms and conditions of this Agreement. End User acknowledges and agrees that CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES may, in its sole discretion, use any method chosen by or available to CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES to verify End User’s compliance with the terms and conditions of this Agreement. During the conduct of such audit, CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES agrees that it will make every effort to avoid unreasonable interference with the conduct of End User’s business.


VIII. EXPORT RESTRICTIONS; COMPLIANCE WITH APPLICABLE LAW

End User acknowledges that the VRISK Software may be subject to United States export laws and regulations. End User acknowledges that it must and will comply with all applicable domestic and international export laws and regulations which are or may become applicable to this software. Such laws may include restrictions on destinations, end users and end use. End User further agrees that it will not use the VRISK Software for any purpose prohibited under applicable law. End User hereby agrees to indemnify, defend and hold harmless CYBER INNOVATIVE TECHNOLOGIES in the event of any claim which may result from End User’s failure to comply with any applicable laws or regulations.


