XIII. U.S. GOVERNMENT USE AND RIGHTS

The Software which is the subject of this Agreement is deemed to be "commercial computer software" and "commercial computer software documentation," as those terms are used in 48 C.F.R. 12.212 and/or 48 C.F.R. 227.7202, as applicable. Consistent with those provisions, such "commercial computer software" and "commercial computer software documentation," are licensed to the government solely under the terms of this Agreement, and any use, modification, reproduction, release, performance, display or disclosure of the VRISK Software and its accompanying documentation is prohibited, except as otherwise provided by the terms of this Agreement, or as agreed to in writing by the parties.


